ects of the Gulag, and show how these lives intertwined. It also sheds new light on the life and works of Chekhov, Gorky, A. Tolstoy, and Bunin.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Jun 2021) 0aAuthors, RussianzFrancevCorrespondence. 0aRussianszFrancevCorrespondence. 7aLITERARY COLLECTIONS / Letters.2bisacsh  a1917 Revolution.  aBunin.  aChekhov.  aCherry Orchard.  aGorky.  aKulman.  aMityas Love.  aNobel Prize.  aParis.  aRussian civil war.  aRussian emigration.  aSoviet Union.  aSt Petersburg.  aTolstoy.  aarchives.  acorrespondence.  aexile.  ahistory.  aletters.  aliterary influences.  aliterature.  amemory.  anobility.  anovel.  aphilology.  apolitics.  atragedy.  awriting.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311068820708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2z978311069629508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020 Englishz978311070474708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2020z9783110704532oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPP ROW Ebook Package English 2020z978311069630140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781644694336zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644694336423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781644694336.jpg  a978-3-11-068820-7  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-069629-5  DG Plus PP Package 2020 Part 2b2020  a978-3-